Being a Whovian, and not a New-Whovian at that, I was excited to learn that this cafe was nearby.  I kept meaning to come here, and see it. My work schedule keeps me out of town a lot, so it has been difficult, thus the anticipation grew.  This week I was finally able to visit this cafe, I read reviews and everything seemed positive.  I also follow their Facebook Page, so I see that they’re proactive in hosting events.  I arrived and I felt a twinge of disappointment with the decor, I felt like more could be done, but then again, a lot of Doctor Who is proprietary, so I understand.  I looked at the menu and again, disappointing, there was nothing that included The Doctor’s name or even one of the many names he’s been called.  I ordered something simple Soup of the Day: Bacon Potato(it was more like assisted living facility potato soup, no bacon, and bland), Dalek Delight(doused with way too much mayo, and looked like it was put together last minute) and a Latte(simple, yet they went so wrong with it, I wasn’t able to finish even 1/4th, not sure if they tried to use regular coffee as espresso or the espresso beans they used were not good, either way, it tasted like old, stale coffee).  As I waited for my food, I noticed that the tables were dirty as was the floor, I would understand if they were busy, people line out the door-only had 2 people working-rush hour. However it was not, there seemed to be 4 employees working, one at the till, two making sandwiches and one making coffee. Making it seem like the employees did not care to the state of the cafe, so long they’re making money.  Once I got my coffee, that’s when I tasted the monstrosity. I didn’t make a fuss, because I thought “maybe it’s just me, since I just brushed my teeth”.  I received my food, and the soup was nice and hot, steaming, I really liked that; however when I tasted it, it had no taste, I felt like the just added the ingredients to the pot without any condiments or giving them time to boil separately to let the flavours simmer. There was also NO BACON, again, I didn’t make a fuss, because everyone has a bad day.  While the sandwich tasted ok, there was more mayo that I would’ve liked, I thought it was going to come on a brioche bun or at least a sub bun, but nope, it came on toast; like they suddenly ran out of buns and they went to the grocery store and bought a loaf of bread. The way the sandwich is described I thought I was going to get this “Grand” sandwich.  It’s been almost 2hrs since I left the cafe, and I’m still not able to finish drinking the coffee.  I’m sure the owner did not have this in mind when he/she opened the cafe. While I was in there I didn’t feel a sense of pride, it seemed as if the decor was an afterthought, by adding knickknacks on shelves, ledges, some pictures on the walls...and the employees didn’t help by not cleaning the tables or floor. I almost felt compelled to ask them for a broom to help them clean.  I will sadly not be returning here again. Hope they make the necessary changes to have a successful place of business, as it does have great potential. Maybe it has gotten complacent due to the fact that it’s somewhere where there’s not much around it to compete with it, but I feel like they need to step it up.
